This paper deals with information theoretic security and side-channel attacks on a cipher system, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of sensors and signal estimation, which could be related to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of bounded storage and strong converse theorems, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT) as well.
